FBIS3-54649 "drsov001_i_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-001 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Jan 1994 CENTRAL ASIA Kazakhstan Specialists Say Military Doctrine `Defense Oriented' LD0201225394 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1930 GMT 2 Jan 94 LD0201225394 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [From the "Radio Slavyanka" program of the Russian Defense Ministry] [Text] Kazakhstan is as yet the only state in Central Asia that has adopted its own military doctrine. The document expounds a system of views on preventing war and on the development of national armed forces. Specialists consider Kazakhstan's military doctrine to be defense oriented and propose cooperating with the CIS countries and tackling common tasks in the military sphere. Multilateral and bilateral intergovernmental agreements and treaties should serve as the legal basis for interaction with the CIS countries in the defense sphere.
